html2canvas is updated to grab/draw mouse-icon in the screenshot.

Part of screen sharing demo, now has realtime mouse icon in the
snapshots.

https://github.com/muaz-khan/WebRTC-Experiment/tree/master/part-of-screen-sharing

You can disable mouse-icon as follownig snippet:

html2canvas(divToShare, {
-- grabMouse: false,
--  onrendered: function(canvas) { }
});

Demo (p2p):
https://www.webrtc-experiment.com/RTCMultiConnection/RTCMultiConnection.sharePartOfScreen.html

RecordRTC breaking updates: Videos tracks are auto-skipped for audio recordings.

You must always pass {type:video} for audio+video (i.e. webm) recording;
otherwise pass {type:audio} to record only audio in ogg format.
RecordRTC will skip video tracks for ogg recordings.

// stream.getVideoTracks().length == 1
// stream.getAudioTracks().length == 1

// recording only audio
var audioRecorder = RecordRTC(stream, {
---- type: 'audio'
});

// recording audio+video
var videoRecorder = RecordRTC(stream, {
---- type: 'video'
});

